<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16868] Avoid appending table to a peer which replicates all tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16868</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;First add a new peer by shell cmd.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
add_peer &apos;1&apos;, CLUSTER_KEY =&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;server1.cie.com:2181:/hbase&quot;&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If we don&apos;t set namespaces and table cfs in peer config. It means replicate all tables to the peer cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then append a table to the peer config.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
append_peer_tableCFs &apos;1&apos;, {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;table1&quot;&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt; []}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then this peer will only replicate table1 to the peer cluster. It changes to replicate only one table from replicate all tables in the cluster. It is very easy to misuse in production cluster. So we should avoid appending table to a peer which replicates all table.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
